Life Insurance and Long Term Care Coverage Overview














                                                        
                                                       
                                                           Term Life Insurance
                                                        

                                           

			Term Life Insurance from Fidelity is designed to provide financial resources to your family in the event of your death.
		














Coverage features



May be appropriate for

Individuals seeking income replacement protection during their working years to help protect their dependents. Insurance benefits would be available to meet needs such as debt obligations and expenses in the event of premature death



Terms available

10, 15, and 20 years



Available to

Residents of all 50 states and the District of Columbia Ages 18 to 70 years1



Minimum coverage

$250,000



Cost (premiums)

Determined by health, family medical history, lifestyle, and other factors



Payment options2

Monthly, semiannually, annually




Fidelity Investments Life Insurance Company ratings



A.M. Best

					
						A+ (Superior) rating3



Standard & Poor's

					
						A+ (Strong) rating3





